Topic \# 1 \\
\begin{center}
Critical Essay Proposal
\end{center}
For the critical essay I will be applying psychoanalytic and feminist criticism to the novel "Disgrace" by J.M. Coetzee. The thesis of the essay will roughly be: In the novel Disgrace by J.M. Coetzee, David Lurie, a stubborn misogynistic man who's "temperament is not going to change, [as] he is too old for that", is taken through a series of events which help him overcome his fear of intimacy as well as develop a respect for woman. I will argue this by establishing the ways in which David's fear of intimacy is implied, such as his obsession with sex and it's passionless form. From then I will show he's misogynistic ways, such as the rape of Melanie. I will then show the ways in which the both are interconnected and finish by showing how David is able to overcome his fear of intimacy by gaining a perspective of woman he lacked.


